{
  "texts": [
    "After evaluating LLMs' generation success rates on the task, we choose to conduct further experiments using only ChatGPT and Alpaca for letter generations.",
    "Analysis on CLG evaluates biases in model generations when given minimal context information, and acts as a lens to interpret underlying biases in models' learned distribution.",
    "Prompting (Brown et al., 2020; Sun and Lai, 2020) steers pre-trained language models with taskspecific instructions to generate task outputs without task fine-tuning.",
    "In our experiments, we de-",
    "Since only 120 letters were generated for preliminary CLG analysis, running statistics analysis on biases in lexical content or word choices might lack significance as we calculate OR for one word at a time."
  ]
}